Analysis of French language texts from academic discourse or media domain to practically functional text genres, applying the methods of text linguistics and of discourse analysis. The object of analysis is text structure as well as the functioning of a text in its specific social contexts.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to develop the skills of analytical reading of texts. For this purpose, methods of text linguistics and discourse analysis are introduced.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has successfully completed the course is able to describe the linguistic, structural, stylistic and discursive features of various kinds of texts and is able to analyze the set of functioning of these texts.
